{"title_page": "Bj\u00f6rk Orchestral", "text_new": "{{Infobox concert|concert_tour_name=Bj\u00f6rk Orchestral|image=BjorkOrchestral.jpg|image_size=220px|image_caption=Official poster for Bj\u00f6rk Orchestral|artist=[[Bj\u00f6rk]]|start_date={{Start date|2020|07|2}}|end_date={{End date|2020|07|20}}|number_of_shows=4 in Europe|last_tour=[[Cornucopia (Bj\u00f6rk concert tour)|Cornucopia]]<br />(2019)|this_tour='''Bj\u00f6rk Orchestral'''<br />(2020)|next_tour=}}\n\n'''Bj\u00f6rk Orchestral''' is the upcoming eleventh [[concert tour]] by Icelandic singer and songwriter [[Bj\u00f6rk]]. Six shows have been announced so far. The tour is set to begin on July 2, 2020 in [[Moscow]], [[Russia]] and conclude on July 20, 2020 in [[Paris]], [[France]].\n\nThe tour was preceded by the announcement of Bj\u00f6rk's performance at the [[Bluedot Festival]], which she's going to headline on the closing night.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Murray |first1=Robin |title=Bj\u00f6rk Confirms Orchestral Tour |url=https://www.clashmusic.com/live/bj%C3%B6rk-confirms-orchestral-tour |website=Clash |accessdate=25 February 2020 |date=25 February 2020}}</ref> The performances were described in contrast to [[Cornucopia (Bj\u00f6rk concert tour)|Cornucopia]], Bj\u00f6rk's latest concert tour, which featured an immersive show production, as they're expected to feature only the singer backed by a local [[orchestra]]. The show is set to feature orchestral arrangements of songs from Bj\u00f6rk's career so far.<ref>{{cite web |title=Billets de concert pour Bj\u00f6rk |url=https://www.livenation.fr/artist/bj%C3%B6rk-tickets |website=livenation.fr |accessdate=25 February 2020 |language=French}}</ref>\n\n== Tour dates ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em;\"| City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\"| Venue\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\"|