in|date=25 February 2020|website=Rolling Stone|language=German|accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.de/20200416/germany-bans-major-events-until-end-of-august-what-you-need-to-know-coronavirus|title=Germany bans major events until end of August: What you need to know|last=|first=|date=|website=www.thelocal.de|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discoverthebluedot.com/?fbclid=IwAR1mmGLPHXNu8LdNDMrvJRbNkJr1EiXPef3KlTVBapiZaNpNS672PPk-W00|title=A message from the bluedot team|website=Bluedot Festival|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n|-\n| 9 July 2020\n|[[Berlin]]\n|[[Germany]]\n|[[Waldb\u00fchne]]\n|[[Berlin Radio Symphony Orchestra|Rundfunk-Sinfonieorchester Berlin]]\n|\u2014\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany]]\n|-\n|26 July 2020{{efn|The 26 July 2020, concert in Cheshire, England at Jodrell Bank Observatory is a part of [[Bluedot Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Aubrey |first1=Elizabeth |title=Bj\u00f6rk, Groove Armada and Metronomy to headline this year\u2019s Bluedot Festival |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/bluedot-confirms-huge-summer-line-up-with-bjork-metronomy-and-groove-armada-headlining-2607879 |website=NME |accessdate=25 February 2020 |date=12 February 2020}}</ref>}}\n|[[Cheshire]]\n|[[England]]\n|[[Jodrell Bank Observatory]]\n|[[The Hall\u00e9]]\n|July 2021\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom]]\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://bjork.com/home#!page=gigography Bjork.com &gt; Past &gt; Gigography]\n\n{{Bjork}}\n\n[[Category:2020 concert tours]]\n[[Category:Bj\u00f6rk concert tours]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox concert|concert_tour_name=Bj\u00f6rk Orchestral|image=BjorkOrchestral.jpg|image_size=220px|image_caption=Official poster for Bj\u00f6rk Orchestral|artist=[[Bj\u00f6rk]]|start_date={{Start date|2020|07|2}}|end_date={{End date|2020|07|20}}|number_